<strong>A:</strong> The 3rd edition incorporates the latest research and trends in strategic management. It also includes new case studies, updated content, and an enhanced focus on the role of technology and innovation in shaping business strategy.</p>
<p><strong>Q: How is the textbook structured?</strong>
<strong>A:</strong> The book is divided into four parts. Part 1 provides an overview of strategic management concepts. Part 2 explores the process of strategic analysis. Part 3 focuses on strategy formulation and implementation. Part 4 addresses strategy control and evaluation.</p>
<p><strong>Q: Who is the target audience for this textbook?</strong>
<strong>A:</strong> The textbook is intended for students and practitioners of strategic management in Southern Africa. It is an essential resource for business schools, universities, and organizations seeking to develop and implement effective strategies in the region.</p>
